#lang racket

#|
PROBLEM 30 - DIGIT FIFTH POWER

surprisingly there are only 3 numbers that can be written as the sum of fourth powers of
their digits

1634 = 1^4 + 6^4 + 3^4 + 4^4
8208 = 8^4 + 2^4 + 0^4 + 8^4
9474 = 9^4 + 4^4 + 7^4 + 4^4

as 1 = 1^4 is not a sum so its not included

the sum of these numbers is 1634+8208+9474 = 19316
find the sum of all the numbers that cna be written as the sum of fifth powers of their digits

answer:

ok let me understand the quetsion
we wanna find sum of all nums that can be written as the sum of fifts powers of their digits

so we know in n^4 example

1634 -> 1 + 1296 + 81 + 256 -> sum them back

UPPER BOUND
59049 * 4 -> 236196 (6 digit)
59049 * 5 -> 295245 (6 digit)
59049 * 6 -> 354294 (6 digit)
59049 * 7 -> 413343  (6 digit)

its impossible for 7 digit number to be equal its own gifit fifth power sum
upper bound is in 6 digit range

You have an upper bound to search up to
For each number in that range, you need to check
if it equals the sum of the fifth powers of its digits
If it does, include it in your final sum


|#

; given a posint n and pow, checks of its equal
(define (is-digit-equal-sum-of-n-pow? n pow)
  ; number -> number
  (define (sum-helper curr-n result)
    (cond [(<= curr-n 0) result]
          [else (sum-helper (quotient curr-n 10) (+ (expt (remainder curr-n 10) pow) result ) ) ]
          )
    ; on each step, strip the last digit and add it to result
    ; divide by 10 and get the digit througuh remainder
    )
  ; check with equal
  (= (sum-helper n 0) n)
  )
(is-digit-equal-sum-of-n-pow? 1634 4) ; #t
(is-digit-equal-sum-of-n-pow? 8208 4) ; #t
(is-digit-equal-sum-of-n-pow? 9474 4) ; #t


; finds the sum of all numbers that can be written as sum of fifth powers of their digits
(define (digit-fifth-power)
  ; lets keep high bound 400k
  (define (helper curr-n sum-so-far)
    (cond [(> curr-n 400000) sum-so-far]
          [(is-digit-equal-sum-of-n-pow? curr-n 5) (helper (+ curr-n 1) (+ curr-n sum-so-far))] ;add it to the sum
          [else (helper (+ curr-n 1) sum-so-far)]
          )
    )
  (helper 10 0)
  )
(digit-fifth-power)
